      "side": 1,
      "message": "It all depends on your overall model/approach and I might not understand what you are going for. \n\nIMO there is another higher level of abstraction missing. Let\u0027s call it a Task (since I think it coincides with what we already call a task in gen_tasks.go). Alternatively a task could also be just a sequence of steps. \n\nTask \n  |\n  |..Step 1\n  |..Step 2\n  |..Step 3\n  |..Step 4\n  ... \n\nSo you runner which I am assuming this program might look something like this:\n\n - instantiate a task and all the steps that make up the task \n - instantiate the receiver(s) \n - run all the steps where each step takes an input \n   (that could be a message or the result of a previous step) and produces a well defined \n   output\n - At the end the task has either succeeded or failed based on the return values of the \n   task",
